title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[m_{\alpha }(x)=x^{n}+c_{n-1}x^{n-1}+…+c_{1}x+c_{0}]]></fr:tex>
be the <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-000X.xml"
addr="nt-000X"
title="Minimal Polynomial for Algebraic Element">minimal polynomial</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ]]></fr:tex> over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk ]]></fr:tex>. Since <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> is algebraic, the coefficients <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[c_{i}]]></fr:tex> are algebraic over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>, and so
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}'=\mathbb {F}(c_{0},…,c_{n-1})]]></fr:tex>
is a finite extension of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk ]]></fr:tex> (since <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-0014.xml"
addr="nt-0014"
title="An extension is finite iff it is finitely-generated by algebraic elements">finitely-generated extensions with algebraic primitives is an algebraic extension</fr:link>).</fr:p>
<fr:p>Since <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m_{\alpha }(x)]]></fr:tex> is irreducible over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk ]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}'\subseteq \Bbbk ]]></fr:tex>, it's also irreducible over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}']]></fr:tex>. Then
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}'(\alpha )\cong \mathbb {F}'[x]/(m_{\alpha }(x))]]></fr:tex>
and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[[\mathbb {F}'(\alpha ) : \mathbb {F}']=n]]></fr:tex>. Since <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-0011.xml"
addr="nt-0011"
title="Degree of Field Extensions is Multiplicative">degree of fields is multiplicative</fr:link>, we see
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[[\mathbb {F}'(\alpha ) : \mathbb {F}]=[\mathbb {F}'(\alpha ) : \mathbb {F}'][\mathbb {F}' : \mathbb {F}]<\infty ,]]></fr:tex>
so <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}'(\alpha )/\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> is a finite extension, <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-0010.xml"
addr="nt-0010"
title="Finite field extensions are algebraic">hence it's an algebraic extension</fr:link>. In particular, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha ]]></fr:tex> is algebraic over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p><html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
class="qed">∎</html:span></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter><fr:tree
